y had a cast of transvestites strike iconic poses on either side of a morbidly obese individual wearing a crown-like halo.\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1215, \"end\": 1229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obesity\", \"score\": 0.9998740637605118, \"rank\": 0.00012595210141208064, \"text\": \"morbidly obese\", \"types\": [\"Q12136\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obesity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Obesity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Christ\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1122}, {\"ngram\": \"his apostles\", \"from\": 1127, \"to\": 1139}, {\"ngram\": \"Jolly\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"a cast\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1157}, {\"ngram\": \"transvestites\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1174}, {\"ngram\": \"iconic poses\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1194}, {\"ngram\": \"either side\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1209}, {\"ngram\": \"a crown-like halo\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1266}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'They attempt, in fact, to obdurate the very principle of the divine.'\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1341, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1293}, {\"ngram\": \"the very principle\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1325}, {\"ngram\": \"the divine\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1339}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Later, a virtually naked man painted blue - who was apparently supposed to be Dionysus, the Greek god of wine-making and ritual madness - who was set upon the table on a plate in front of the mock apostolate proceeded to sing.\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1569, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1421, \"end\": 1429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1121555288401416e-27, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 1435, \"end\": 1440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9282159878374535, \"rank\": 0.07490955325488671, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a virtually naked man\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1371}, {\"ngram\": \"wine-making and ritual madness\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1478}, {\"ngram\": \"the table\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1507}, {\"ngram\": \"a plate\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1518}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1527}, {\"ngram\": \"the mock apostolate\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1550}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a recent op-ed for Blaze News, Sen. Mike Lee (R-Utah)noted: Newly baptized actor and podcast host Russell Brandrecentlyponderedprecisely what symbols these would-be conquerors are attempting to advance as well as what is ultimately at the heart of the French's latest cultish display.\", \"from\": 1573, \"to\": 1861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1612, \"end\": 1620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Lee_(New_Zealand_politician)\", \"score\": 0.4973884692646734, \"rank\": 0.6197916666666509, \"text\": \"Mike Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Lee_(New_Zealand_politician)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Lee_(New_Zealand_politician)\"}, {\"begin\": 1675, \"end\": 1682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bertrand_Russell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.924818970087935e-28, \"text\": \"Russell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bertrand_Russell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bertrand_Russell\"}, {\"begin\": 1829, \"end\": 1835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9714509771458368, \"rank\": 0.02705894488944883, \