rom\": 2478, \"to\": 2485}, {\"ngram\": \"edicts\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2496}, {\"ngram\": \"the apex\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2509}, {\"ngram\": \"supreme hierarchy\", \"from\": 2514, \"to\": 2531}, {\"ngram\": \"ideologies\", \"from\": 2535, \"to\": 2545}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That there is nothing superior and supreme to which we have to surrender?\\\"\", \"from\": 2547, \"to\": 2621, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2568}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brand concluded that what is behind this propaganda is in line with the project of the Paris' 18th century cultists of reason: to \\\"derail the sacred and engender a kind of state of nihilism where everything might be regarded as a truth.\\\"\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2710, \"end\": 2715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990391188, \"rank\": 9.607186553125734e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Brand\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2628}, {\"ngram\": \"this propaganda\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2674}, {\"ngram\": \"line\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2685}, {\"ngram\": \"the project\", \"from\": 2691, \"to\": 2702}, {\"ngram\": \"reason\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2748}, {\"ngram\": \"a kind\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2791}, {\"ngram\": \"state\", \"from\": 2795, \"to\": 2800}, {\"ngram\": \"nihilism\", \"from\": 2804, \"to\": 2812}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 2819, \"to\": 2829}, {\"ngram\": \"a truth\", \"from\": 2851, \"to\": 2858}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the podcast host later indicated he was not altogether convinced that the coloration of the Dionysus character in a corpse-like color and his presentation as a meal was intended to be a direct mockery of the Eucharist, he said the display was at the very least oriented toward \\\"nihilism, unbelief, celebration of selfishness.\\\"\", \"from\": 2862, \"to\": 3194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2960, \"end\": 2968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1121555288401416e-27, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 3076, \"end\": 3085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"score\": 0.9196200130616118, \"rank\": 0.08740560655814016, \"text\": \"Eucharist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the podcast host\", \"from\": 2868, \"to\": 2884}, {\"ngram\": \"the coloration\", \"from\": 2938, \"to\": 2952}, {\"ngram\": \"a corpse-like color\", \"from\": 2982, \"to\": 3001}, {\"ngram\": \"his presentation\", \"from\": 3006, \"to\": 3022}, {\"ngram\": \"a meal\", \"from\": 3026, \"to\": 3032}, {\"ngram\": \"a direct mockery\", \"from\": 3052, \"to\": 3068}, {\"ngram\": \"the display\", \"from\": 3095, \"to\": 3106}, {\"ngram\": \"nihilism\", \"from\": 3146, \"to\": 3154}, {\"ngram\": \"unbelief\", \"from\": 3156, \"to\": 3164}, {\"ngram\": \"celebration\", \"from\": 3166, \"to\": 3177}, {\"ngram\": \"selfishness\", \"from\": 3181, \"to\": 3192}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the basis of Brand's comments in a video posted Wednesday to his X account, it appears he regards this nihilistic project as a trap for the soul.\", \"from\": 3196, \"to\": 3344, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the basis\", \"from\": 3199, \"to\": 3208}, {\"ngram\": \"Brand's comments\", \"from\": 3212, \"to\": 3228}, {\"ngram\": \"a video\", \"from\": 3232, \"to\": 3239}, {\"ngram\": \"his X account\", \"from\": 3260, \"to\": 3273}, {\"ngram\": \"this nihilistic project\", \"from\": 3297, \"to\": 3320}, {\"ngram\": \"a trap\", \"from\": 3324, \"to\": 3330}, {\"ngram\": \"the soul\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3343}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are times when I have told you that I felt far for Christ,\\\"saidBrand.\", \"from\": 3346, \"to\": 3422, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3362}, {\"ngram\": \"Christ,\\\"saidBrand\", \"from\": 3404, \"to\": 3421}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is a verse that brought me back into connection with our Lord.\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3491, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a verse\", \"from\": 3432, \"to\": 3439}, {\"ngram\": \"connection\", \"from\": 3466, \"to\": 3476}, {\"ngram\": \"our Lord\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3490}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's from Isaiah.\", \"from\": 3492, \"to\": 3509, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3502, \"end\": 3508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaiah\", \"score\": 0.9999933881286176, \"rank\": 6.611915191795898e-06, \"text\": \"Isaiah\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaiah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaiah\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Fear not, for I have redeemed you.\", \"from\": 3510, \"to\": 3545, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have called you by your name.\", \"from\": 3546, \"to\": 3577, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your name\", \"from\": 3567, \"to\": 3576}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You are mine.'\\\"\", \"from\": 3578, \"to\": 3593, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My feelings of faith have altered lately because I have had the sense that through fear I might take back my self will, that I might, through fear, think I have to be in control of the situation,\\\" continued Brand.\", \"from\": 3595, \"to\": 3809, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My feelings\", \"from\": 3596, \"to\": 3607}, {\"ngram\": \"faith\", \"from\": 3611, \"to\": 3616}, {\"ngram\": \"the sense\", \"from\": 3656, \"to\": 3665}, {\"ngram\": \"fear\", \"from\": 3679, \"to\": 3683}, {\"ngram\": \"my self\", \"from\": 3702, \"to\": 3709}, {\"ngram\": \"fear\", \"from\": 3738, \"to\": 3742}, {\"ngram\": \"control\", \"from\": 3766, \"to\": 3773}, {\"ngram\": \"the situation\", \"from\": 3777, \"to\": 3790}, {\"ngram\": \"Brand\", \"from\": 3803, \"to\": 3808}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If you feel that you are being attacked, if you are under threat, it seems obvious, rational, sensible, to take back control.\\\"\", \"from\": 3810, \"to\": 3937, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"threat\", \"from\": 3869, \"to\": 3875}, {\"ngram\": \"control\", \"from\": 3928, \"to\": 3935}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But the sensation of faith - allowing Christ in His sub-molecular potency, right down to the granule, right out into the cosmological, to order all things, for we are dealing with the king of eternity,\\\" added Brand.\", \"from\": 3939, \"to\": 4155, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sensation\", \"from\": 3944, \"to\": 3957}, {\"ngram\": \"faith\", \"from\": 3961, \"to\": 3966}, {\"ngram\": \"Christ\", \"from\": 3978, \"to\": 3984}, {\"ngram\": \"His sub-molecular potency\", \"from\": 3988, \"to\": 4013}, {\"ngram\": \"the granule\", \"from\": 4029, \"to\": 4040}, {\"ngram\": \"the cosmological\", \"from\": 4057, \"to\": 4073}, {\"ngram\": \"all things\", \"from\": 4084, \"to\": 4094}, {\"ngram\": \"the king\", \"from\": 4120, \"to\": 4128}, {\"ngram\": \"eternity\", \"from\": 4132, \"to\": 4140}, {\"ngram\": \"Brand\", \"from\": 4149, \"to\": 4154}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brand noted that surrender to Christ means liberation from \\\"the cubic reality afforded to you by materialism and rationalism, and into a transcendent realm where you are given grace - where once I have accepted sin and surrendered, and allowed Him to carry me, I am granted a new freedom.\", \"from\